blocks.text: So when you change in Master it will reflect on its Children right away.
Master must be kept in canvas in order to have a full control over its Children.
if you removed the Master from the canvas you will have to go to every child you had made
You can override on the child as much as you can
BUT the overridden child will not take orders from their master again.
You can reset overridden properties and switch back to their Master properties.
You can detach the link between Master and its Children.

blocks.text: It's the same concept of Symbols in Sketch or Components in Figma.
A quick way to save time when we design something.
In Framer we create a component of elements in our design to use it
as much as we can with the ability to
customise the properties like colour, opacity and radius, or layout options like size.
